               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="183609190122"></xptr>
               <p>prisoner was his servant—in consequence of a from my brother, I found that he had lost 33 1/2 lbs. of tallow—I have seen it at the station-house—this is it—I know it from having seen it on the Saturday after<lb></lb>noon preceding the Sunday it was stolen—I noticed these black marks, which are defects in it.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Prisoner.</hi> I took one bit to try an experiment at home, the other piece is not yours. <hi rend="italic">Witness.</hi> I cannot swear to this other piece, but to this one I can.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18360919-name-784" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-784" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-784" type="surname" value="FRANKLIN"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18360919-name-784" type="given" value="CHARLES"></interp>CHARLES FRANKLIN</persName>
                  </hi>. I was on duty in Windsor-terrace, City-road, and stopped the prisoner, coming from Mr. Wilkinson's premises—he had this piece and another with him—I took him back, and he threw one into the vat that was melting while I was there—he ran away, and threw it in, and then I caught him again.</p>
               <p>(The prisoner received a good character.)</p>
